article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- — Sam Brown's 26 points helped Pennsylvania defeat Dartmouth 82-69 on Friday night. Brown added five assists for the Quakers (10-15, 2-8 Ivy League). Cam Thrower scored 16 points, going 6 of 11 (4 for 9 from 3-point range). Clark Slajchert was 5 of 11 shooting (2 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points. The victory broke an eight-game losing streak for the Quakers. Dusan Neskovic led the way for the Big Green (5-18, 1-9) with 23 points. Jayden Williams added 10 points for Dartmouth. Jackson Munro also had eight points and two blocks. The loss is the sixth straight for the Big Green. Both teams next play Saturday. Pennsylvania visits Harvard and Dartmouth squares off against Princeton at home. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
